2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the properties of families of sets and their incidence matrices, which are relevant to the study of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper presents bounds on the rate of disjunctive codes, which can be seen as a measure of the complexity of encoding and decoding information. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper's focus on binary codes and their properties may have applications in cryptography and security. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper's use of set theory and combinatorics suggests a connection to discrete mathematics.
